Lin's has all kinds of snacks - both Hawaiian and non-Hawaiian. If you're visiting Hawaii, it would be a great place to get some local snacks here and bring them home as souvenirs. Prices vary - some are reasonable, but others can be pretty high. There are some snack items here that you could find for much cheaper at an Asian grocery store.  They've also got shave ice and bubble tea, but I usually just come for all the different kinds of candy. Even if you don't have a sweet tooth, you will probably leave with one,
